From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rudi Heitbaum <rudi.heitbaum@sparknel-dc.com.au>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dtoc: handle non-ASCII files without warnings

src_scan opens every .c and .h file in the tree looking for
U_BOOT_DRIVER/UCLASS_DRIVER/struct macros. Files that contain invalid
UTF-8 byte sequences trigger a UnicodeDecodeError and are silently
skipped with a 'Skipping file ... due to unicode error' message.

Using errors='replace' lets Python substitute the replacement character
(U+FFFD) for any invalid byte sequence instead of raising an exception.
The replacement character never appears in a macro name so parsing is
unaffected; files that contain no relevant macros are still skipped by
the existing 'U_BOOT_DRIVER'/'struct' guards.

The existing test_unicode_error test exercises this path with a \x81
byte and continues to pass: the file is read with a replacement
character and the macro guards skip it, same as before.

This silences the spurious warnings produced for lwip headers that
carry non-ASCII author names in their copyright lines.

Signed-off-by: Rudi Heitbaum <rudi.heitbaum@sparknel-dc.com.au>
---
 tools/dtoc/src_scan.py | 18 ++++--------------
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/dtoc/src_scan.py b/tools/dtoc/src_scan.py
--- a/tools/dtoc/src_scan.py
+++ b/tools/dtoc/src_scan.py
@@ -621,13 +621,8 @@ class Scanner:
         Args
             fname: Driver filename to scan
         """
-        with open(fname, encoding='utf-8') as inf:
-            try:
-                buff = inf.read()
-            except UnicodeDecodeError:
-                # This seems to happen on older Python versions
-                print("Skipping file '%s' due to unicode error" % fname)
-                return
+        with open(fname, encoding='utf-8', errors='replace') as inf:
+            buff = inf.read()

             # If this file has any U_BOOT_DRIVER() declarations, process it to
             # obtain driver information
@@ -646,13 +641,8 @@ class Scanner:
         Args
             fname: header filename to scan
         """
-        with open(fname, encoding='utf-8') as inf:
-            try:
-                buff = inf.read()
-            except UnicodeDecodeError:
-                # This seems to happen on older Python versions
-                print("Skipping file '%s' due to unicode error" % fname)
-                return
+        with open(fname, encoding='utf-8', errors='replace') as inf:
+            buff = inf.read()

             # If this file has any U_BOOT_DRIVER() declarations, process it to
             # obtain driver information
